wikipedia_page.main: Sir Harry Ralph Selley (9 December 1871 – 24 February 1960) was a British master builder and Conservative Party politician.  He served as the Member of Parliament (MP) for Battersea South in London from 1931 to 1945.

List of MPs elected in the 1935 United Kingdom general election

response: The local Liberal association selected 40 year-old Vivian Claude Albu as their candidate. Albu had stood for the Liberals in the 1922 general election at Battersea North.The Liberal Year Book, 1926 Labour selected William Bennett, who had been their candidate in Guildford in three general elections between 1918 and 1923. The Conservative Party selected Harry Selley, a builder and member of the London County Council for Battersea South.
